<DOC><DOCNO> AP881225-0001 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-25-88 0000EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a AM-JailDisturbance     12-24 0200</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Jail Disturbance,0205</SECOND><HEAD>Inmates, Upset About Christmas Eve Detention, Set Fires At GeorgiaJail</HEAD><DATELINE>GAINESVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Inmates at the Hall County jail,apparently upset about being locked up on Christmas Eve, staged aprotest Saturday night, setting fires and causing an undeterminedamount of damage before the uprising was ended, authorities said.   The disturbance, which began about 8:30 p.m., was under controlby 11:30 p.m., said Sgt. Ed Barfield, spokesman for the Hall CountySheriff's Department. There were no injuries, he said.   ``They were disgruntled,'' Barfield said. ``It's overcrowdedhere; we've got them one on top of another. It's Christmas. Theywere just disgruntled.''   Barfield said the disturbance occurred in a cell block housingabout 30 inmates. He said he did not know how many participated inthe unrest.   The inmates set fires to mattresses, and ``a good bit of damage''was done to light fixtures and air ducts, he said. There also wasconsiderable water damage.   Barfield said a county SWAT team, as well as city police andstate corrections officials, were called in to help quell thedisturbance.   Officers planned to stay on the scene Sunday morning in casethere was a recurrence, he said.</TEXT></DOC>